File: platform/browser-extension/src/confirmation-badge.ts

The bug is at lines 56-60 in notifyConfirmationRequest():
```
pendingConfirmationCount++;
const bgTimeoutId = setTimeout(...);
confirmationTimeouts.set(id, bgTimeoutId);
```

If `id` already exists in confirmationTimeouts, the old setTimeout handle is overwritten and leaked — it can never be cleared. The leaked timeout fires clearConfirmationBadge() unexpectedly, decrementing pendingConfirmationCount below the actual number of pending confirmations.

Fix: Before incrementing count and setting the new timeout, check if confirmationTimeouts already has the id. If so, clearTimeout the existing handle and do NOT increment pendingConfirmationCount (the count was already incremented on the first call).

The test file is platform/browser-extension/src/confirmation-badge.test.ts (create it if it doesn't exist). Mock setTimeout/clearTimeout and chrome.action.setBadgeText/setBadgeBackgroundColor.
